    confirmation emails as well as a testimonial from us expressing how happy
    we are using their service for payments.


  %h3
    Crowd funding site
  %p
    The Travis CI crowd funding site<sup><a href="#fn-1">1</a></sup> will
    hopefully generate a huge amount of attention and hype over the next few
    weeks.
  %p
    Logos and text ads in the "Thank you, sponsors" section have the following
    layout and sizes and are rotated so each company has an equal opportunity
    to be shown (per package type).
  %p
    %img{src: '/images/banner-sizes-crowd-page.png'}
  %p
    This list is paginated, so curious users can flip through the pages and see
    all the sponsors who are supporting Travis. And after 5 seconds the next
    page is shown automatically.


  %h3
    Application sidebar
  %p
    The sidebar is in the process of being re-designed so that we have two
    spots where sponsors appear.
  %p
    There will be a slot at the top of the sidebar (above the workers list)
    that displays either 1 Platinum or 2 Gold sponsors at a time with a chance
    of 1:2 to display Platinum vs. Gold sponsors.  There will be another list
    of sponsors (below the queues lists) that displays 6 Silver sponsors at a
    time as text links and a link to the Travis CI sponsors
    page<sup><a href="#fn-3">3</a></sup>:
  %p
    %img{src: '/images/banner-sizes-travis-ci.png'}


  %h3
    Build notification emails
  %p
    We display 1 Platinum sponsor or 2 Gold sponsors below every build
    notification email. These are randomized and Platinum sponsors have a
    greater chance to appear over Gold sponsors.
  %p
    And, of course, there will also be a link to the main Travis CI sponsors
    page
    %sup
      %a{href: '#fn-3'} 3


  %h3
    Sponsors page
  %p
    All sponsors will be listed at http://love.travis-ci.org/sponsors in the
    order of their package size (Platinum, Gold, Silver) and in the order of
    their package booking date.
  %p
    Each sponsor entry will contain your logo, your copy (containing links to
    pages of your choice) and the blog post on the Travis CI blog featuring
    your sponsorship (see below).


  %h3
    Blog
  %p
    Platinum and gold sponsors may provide blog posts presenting their company,
    involvement in the open source community and reasons to support Travis CI.
    These blog posts are published without any editing - you write it and we
    put it on our blog. We may stagger publishing of these blog posts as to not
    flood the blog.
  %p
    Platinum sponsors will get their own blog post, while Gold sponsors will
    share a blog post.
  %p
    Silver sponsors may provide a paragraph for a summary post where we thank
    all our Silver sponsors.


  %h3
    Twitter
  %p
    Although we could shout from the roof about how happy we are to have you
    support us, tweeting reaches a larger audience.
  %p
    Once we have added your logo to the crowd funding page we will tweet it out
    to the world from our Travis CI account
    (<a href="http://twitter.com/travisci">@travisci</a>).
  %p
    We also retweet these tweets from at least one of our personal Twitter
    accounts (<a href="http://twitter.com/j2h">@j2h</a>,
    <a href="http://twitter.com/konstantinhaase">@konstantinhaase</a> and
    <a href="http://twitter.com/svenfuchs">@svenfuchs</a>) for Platinum
    and Gold sponsors, and Silver sponsors on special occasions.
  %p
    All of these accounts have 4237 <i>unique</i> followers according to
    <a href="https://github.com/travis-ci/travis-crowd/blob/master/script/followers.rb">this script</a>.


  %h3
    Conference Talks
  %p
    We show our sponsors' logos on slides and read out names in each conference
    talk about Travis CI. We need to fit this to the actual presentation but we
    do our best to draw as much attention to our sponsors as possible.


  %h3
    Office visits and personal stuff
  %p
    The Platinum and Gold packages include the option to have Josh and/or Sven
    and/or Konstantin visit your office and meet your team for pair programming
    sessions or other kinds of events. (You will need to help with travel and
    accommodation if you're not based close to us.)
  %p
    Visiting you is just one idea. We are open for ideas that fit your company
    better, so feel free to
    %a{href: '/#contact'} ask.



  %h3
    Sticker/swag mailing
  %p
    We send out one or many stickers to every donor through snail mail.
  %p
    Platinum and Gold sponsors can contribute own stickers or other swag that
    will be included to these mailings. For items that contribute significant
    size the sponsor might need to help with additional postal charges.

